{"type":"message","id":"be852058","parentId":"bfe1db43","timestamp":"2026-05-07T08:09:11.830Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"แก้ Full Bridge sync จริงระหว่าง Telegram ↔ Discord\n\nโอเค เจ้านายต้องการแบบที่ 2: Full Bridge (สองทางจริง)\n\nตอนนี้จาก AGENTS.md มี bridge อยู่แล้ว:\n- Discord → Telegram: ใช้ dc-to-tg.py (manual relay)\n- Telegram → Discord: bridge.py รัน background\n- ป้องกัน loop: [TG] [DC] prefix\n\nแต่ยังไม่สมบูรณ์ เพราะ:\n1. Discord → Telegram ต้อง manual (dc-to-tg.py) ไม่ใช่ auto\n2. ต้องมี bridge-active file อยู่ถึงจะทำงาน\n3. อาจมีปัญหาเรื่อง duplicate/loop\n\nงานที่ต้องทำ:\n1. ตรวจสอบ bridge ปัจจุบัน\n2. ทำให้ Discord → Telegram เป็น auto relay\n3. ปรับปรุงให้สองทาง sync จริง\n4. ป้องกัน loop อย่างมีประสิทธิภาพ\n5. สร้าง bridge-active indicator\n\nเริ่มด้วยการดูไฟล์ bridge ที่มีอยู่ก่อน","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"🧑🏼‍💻 เจ้านายต้องการ Full Bridge sync จริงสองทางเลยครับ เดี๋ยวตรวจและแก้ให้ 🧑🏼‍💻"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:5","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/bridge* ~/.openclaw/workspace/dc-to-tg* 2>/dev/null"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:6","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/bridge.py 2>/dev/null || echo \"bridge.py not found\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"kimi-k2.6:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778141340118,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778141341897"}}
{"type":"message","id":"ac5b80bf","parentId":"be852058","timestamp":"2026-05-07T08:09:11.902Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.exec:5","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan    7 May  7 14:56 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge-active\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan  417 May  7 14:57 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge.log\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan 4926 May  7 14:54 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge.py\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan  871 May  7 14:55 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/dc-to-tg.py"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":13,"aggregated":"-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan    7 May  7 14:56 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge-active\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan  417 May  7 14:57 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge.log\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan 4926 May  7 14:54 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge.py\n-rw-rw-r-- 1 apinan apinan  871 May  7 14:55 /home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/dc-to-tg.py","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778141351902}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a40d933","parentId":"ac5b80bf","timestamp":"2026-05-07T08:09:11.903Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.exec:6","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTelegram <-> Discord Bridge\nSyncs messages between Telegram DM and Discord DM.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport time\nimport json\nimport requests\nimport sys\n\n# Config\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = \"867401…uE0o\"\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = \"1060942816\"\nDISCORD_TOKEN = ***\"DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\", \"\")\nDISCORD_USER_ID = \"817750913405157406\"\n\nTELEGRAM_API = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}\"\nDISCORD_API = \"https://discord.com/api/v10\"\n\n# State\nlast_update_id = 0\ndiscord_dm_channel_id = None\n\ndef get_discord_dm_channel():\n    \"\"\"Create/get DM channel with the user.\"\"\"\n    global discord_dm_channel_id\n    if discord_dm_channel_id:\n        return discord_dm_channel_id\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    payload = {\"recipient_id\": DISCORD_USER_ID}\n    \n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/users/@me/channels\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json=payload\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        data = r.json()\n        discord_dm_channel_id = data[\"id\"]\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Discord DM channel: {discord_dm_channel_id}\")\n        return discord_dm_channel_id\n    else:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to create DM channel: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n        return None\n\ndef send_to_discord(text):\n    \"\"\"Send message to Discord DM.\"\"\"\n    channel_id = get_discord_dm_channel()\n    if not channel_id:\n        return False\n    \n    # Add prefix to avoid loop\n    if text.startswith(\"[DC] \"):\n        return True  # Skip relaying back Discord messages\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    payload = {\n        \"content\": f\"[TG] {text}\"\n    }\n    \n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/channels/{channel_id}/messages\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json=payload\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Sent to Discord: {text[:50]}\")\n        return True\n    else:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to send Discord: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n        return False\n\ndef poll_telegram():\n    \"\"\"Poll Telegram for new messages.\"\"\"\n    global last_update_id\n    \n    try:\n        params = {\n            \"offset\": last_update_id + 1,\n            \"limit\": 10\n        }\n        r = requests.get(\n            f\"{TELEGRAM_API}/getUpdates\",\n            params=params,\n            timeout=30\n        )\n        \n        if r.status_code != 200:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Telegram poll error: {r.status_code}\")\n            return\n        \n        data = r.json()\n        if not data.get(\"ok\"):\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Telegram API error: {data}\")\n            return\n        \n        updates = data.get(\"result\", [])\n        for update in updates:\n            last_update_id = update[\"update_id\"]\n            \n            # Check if message exists\n            msg = update.get(\"message\")\n            if not msg:\n                continue\n            \n            # Only process from our chat\n            chat = msg.get(\"chat\", {})\n            if str(chat.get(\"id\")) != TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID:\n                continue\n            \n            # Get text\n            text = msg.get(\"text\", \"\")\n            if not text:\n                continue\n            \n            # Skip if it's our own relay message\n            if text.startswith(\"[DC] \"):\n                continue\n            \n            print(f\"[Bridge] TG -> DC: {text[:50]}\")\n            send_to_discord(text)\n            \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Poll error: {e}\")\n\ndef send_to_telegram(text):\n    \"\"\"Send message to Telegram (called externally).\"\"\"\n    if text.startswith(\"[TG] \"):\n        return True  # Skip relaying back Telegram messages\n    \n    try:\n        payload = {\n            \"chat_id\": TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID,\n            \"text\": f\"[DC] {text}\"\n        }\n        r = requests.post(\n            f\"{TELEGRAM_API}/sendMessage\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=10\n        )\n        if r.status_code == 200:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Sent to Telegram: {text[:50]}\")\n            return True\n        else:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to send Telegram: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n            return False\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Send Telegram error: {e}\")\n        return False\n\ndef main():\n    print(\"[Bridge] Starting Telegram <-> Discord bridge...\")\n    \n    if not DISCORD_TOKEN:\n        ***\"[Bridge] ERROR: DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN not set!\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    # Test Discord DM channel\n    channel = get_discord_dm_channel()\n    if not channel:\n        print(\"[Bridge] WARNING: Could not create Discord DM channel\")\n    \n    print(\"[Bridge] Polling started. Press Ctrl+C to stop.\")\n    \n    while True:\n        poll_telegram()\n        time.sleep(2)  # Poll every 2 seconds\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":61,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nTelegram <-> Discord Bridge\nSyncs messages between Telegram DM and Discord DM.\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport time\nimport json\nimport requests\nimport sys\n\n# Config\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = \"8674013658:AAEK6ot7k9xxhoBWFXX5MnpWnA6Jru5uE0o\"\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = \"1060942816\"\nDISCORD_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\", \"\")\nDISCORD_USER_ID = \"817750913405157406\"\n\nTELEGRAM_API = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}\"\nDISCORD_API = \"https://discord.com/api/v10\"\n\n# State\nlast_update_id = 0\ndiscord_dm_channel_id = None\n\ndef get_discord_dm_channel():\n    \"\"\"Create/get DM channel with the user.\"\"\"\n    global discord_dm_channel_id\n    if discord_dm_channel_id:\n        return discord_dm_channel_id\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    payload = {\"recipient_id\": DISCORD_USER_ID}\n    \n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/users/@me/channels\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json=payload\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        data = r.json()\n        discord_dm_channel_id = data[\"id\"]\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Discord DM channel: {discord_dm_channel_id}\")\n        return discord_dm_channel_id\n    else:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to create DM channel: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n        return None\n\ndef send_to_discord(text):\n    \"\"\"Send message to Discord DM.\"\"\"\n    channel_id = get_discord_dm_channel()\n    if not channel_id:\n        return False\n    \n    # Add prefix to avoid loop\n    if text.startswith(\"[DC] \"):\n        return True  # Skip relaying back Discord messages\n    \n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    payload = {\n        \"content\": f\"[TG] {text}\"\n    }\n    \n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/channels/{channel_id}/messages\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json=payload\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Sent to Discord: {text[:50]}\")\n        return True\n    else:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to send Discord: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n        return False\n\ndef poll_telegram():\n    \"\"\"Poll Telegram for new messages.\"\"\"\n    global last_update_id\n    \n    try:\n        params = {\n            \"offset\": last_update_id + 1,\n            \"limit\": 10\n        }\n        r = requests.get(\n            f\"{TELEGRAM_API}/getUpdates\",\n            params=params,\n            timeout=30\n        )\n        \n        if r.status_code != 200:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Telegram poll error: {r.status_code}\")\n            return\n        \n        data = r.json()\n        if not data.get(\"ok\"):\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Telegram API error: {data}\")\n            return\n        \n        updates = data.get(\"result\", [])\n        for update in updates:\n            last_update_id = update[\"update_id\"]\n            \n            # Check if message exists\n            msg = update.get(\"message\")\n            if not msg:\n                continue\n            \n            # Only process from our chat\n            chat = msg.get(\"chat\", {})\n            if str(chat.get(\"id\")) != TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID:\n                continue\n            \n            # Get text\n            text = msg.get(\"text\", \"\")\n            if not text:\n                continue\n            \n            # Skip if it's our own relay message\n            if text.startswith(\"[DC] \"):\n                continue\n            \n            print(f\"[Bridge] TG -> DC: {text[:50]}\")\n            send_to_discord(text)\n            \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Poll error: {e}\")\n\ndef send_to_telegram(text):\n    \"\"\"Send message to Telegram (called externally).\"\"\"\n    if text.startswith(\"[TG] \"):\n        return True  # Skip relaying back Telegram messages\n    \n    try:\n        payload = {\n            \"chat_id\": TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID,\n            \"text\": f\"[DC] {text}\"\n        }\n        r = requests.post(\n            f\"{TELEGRAM_API}/sendMessage\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=10\n        )\n        if r.status_code == 200:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Sent to Telegram: {text[:50]}\")\n            return True\n        else:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to send Telegram: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n            return False\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Send Telegram error: {e}\")\n        return False\n\ndef main():\n    print(\"[Bridge] Starting Telegram <-> Discord bridge...\")\n    \n    if not DISCORD_TOKEN:\n        print(\"[Bridge] ERROR: DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN not set!\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n    \n    # Test Discord DM channel\n    channel = get_discord_dm_channel()\n    if not channel:\n        print(\"[Bridge] WARNING: Could not create Discord DM channel\")\n    \n    print(\"[Bridge] Polling started. Press Ctrl+C to stop.\")\n    \n    while True:\n        poll_telegram()\n        time.sleep(2)  # Poll every 2 seconds\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()","cwd":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1778141351902}}
{"type":"message","id":"b4e57a82","parentId":"9a40d933","timestamp":"2026-05-07T08:09:40.768Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"เจ้านายต้องการ Full Bridge ที่ sync จริงทั้งสองทาง\n\nตอนนี้มี:\n1. bridge.py - รัน background, poll Telegram → Discord (มี loop detection ด้วย [TG]/[DC] prefix)\n2. dc-to-tg.py - manual script สำหรับ Discord → Telegram\n3. bridge-active - file ตัวบ่งชี้ว่า bridge ทำงานอยู่\n\nปัญหาที่เห็น:\n1. bridge.py ใช้ polling (getUpdates) ซึ่ง conflict กับ OpenClaw bot ที่ใช้ webhook/long polling เหมือนกัน - อาจทำให้ bot หลักไม่ได้รับ message\n2. Discord → Telegram ยังเป็น manual ไม่ใช่ auto\n3. bridge.py ใช้ Discord Bot Token ไม่ใช่ User Token ทำให้ส่ง DM ได้แต่อาจมีข้อจำกัด\n\nสิ่งที่ต้องทำเพื่อ Full Bridge:\n1. ใช้ Discord Bot Gateway/Websocket แทน manual polling เพื่อรับ message แบบ real-time\n2. หรือใช้ Discord webhook/ตั้งค่าให้ bot ฟัง message\n3. แต่ต้องระวัง loop\n\nอันที่จริงแล้ว ถ้าใช้ OpenClaw อยู่แล้ว และ OpenClaw มี Discord + Telegram provider ที่ active อยู่ใน gateway เราสามารถใช้ OpenClaw เองเป็น bridge ได้! \n\nแต่จาก AGENTS.md:\n- Discord → Telegram: เมื่อได้รับข้อความจาก Discord ให้ส่งข้อความเดียวกันไป Telegram โดยใช้ python3 dc-to-tg.py\n- Telegram → Discord: bridge.py จะจัดการให้\n\nนั่นหมายความว่า OpenClaw agent รับ message จาก Discord แล้วส่งไป Telegram ด้วย dc-to-tg.py แต่ตอนนี้เป็น manual ไม่ใช่ auto\n\nWait, ดูดีๆแล้ว AGENTS.md บอกว่า bridge.py รัน background จัดการ Telegram → Discord ส่วน Discord → Telegram ต้องใช้ dc-to-tg.py แต่ไม่ชัดว่า OpenClaw จะ trigger dc-to-tg.py auto ยังไง\n\nควรจะทำ:\n1. ให้ bridge.py จัดการทั้งสองทางจริงๆ\n2. ใช้ Discord Gateway websocket เพื่อรับ message แบบ real-time\n3. หรือถ้าใช้ OpenClaw agent รับ message จาก Discord แล้วส่งไป Telegram โดยตรง (ผ่าน message tool หรือ exec dc-to-tg.py)\n\nแต่ถ้า bridge.py รัน standalone เป็น background process มันก็ไม่ conflict กับ OpenClaw bot ที่ใช้ webhook อยู่ ถ้า OpenClaw ใช้ webhook mode ไม่ใช่ polling\n\nเดี๋ยวตรวจสอบก่อนว่า OpenClaw ใช้ webhook หรือ polling\n\nจาก context ดูเหมือน bridge.py ใช้ polling (getUpdates) ซึ่งจะ conflict กับ OpenClaw Telegram provider ที่อาจใช้ polling/webhook อยู่\n\nถ้าจะทำ Full Bridge จริงๆ ต้อง:\n1. ตรวจสอบว่า OpenClaw ใช้ Telegram polling หรือ webhook\n2. ถ้าใช้ polling → bridge.py จะ conflict (getUpdates ตัวเดียวกัน ใครดึงก่อนได้ก่อน)\n3. ถ้าใช้ webhook → bridge.py ใช้ polling ได้\n\nแต่ถ้าเราใช้วิธีที่ OpenClaw agent เองเป็น bridge (รับจาก Discord แล้วส่งไป Telegram ผ่าน message tool) ก็ไม่ต้องใช้ bridge.py polling เลย\n\nเดี๋ยวดู dc-to-tg.py ก่อนแล้วคิดต่อ","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/dc-to-tg.py 2>/dev/null || echo \"not found\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:8","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat ~/.openclaw/workspace/bridge-active 2>/dev/null || echo \"not found\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:9","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -i bridge | grep -v grep"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"kimi-k2.6:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778141351904,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778141355412"}}
{"type":"message","id":"44901ca9","parentId":"b4e57a82","timestamp":"2026-05-07T08:09:40.814Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"functions.exec:7","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Send Discord message to Telegram\"\"\"\nimport requests\nimport sys\n\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = \"867401…uE0o\"\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = \"1060942816\"\n\ndef send_to_telegram(text):\n    if text.startswith(\"[TG] \"):\n        return True\n    \n    try:\n        payload = {\n            \"chat_id\": TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID,\n            \"text\": f\"[DC] {text}\"\n        }\n        r = requests.post(\n            f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/sendMessage\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=10\n        )\n        return r.status_code == 200\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return False\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    text = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else sys.stdin.read().strip()\n    if text:\n        ok = send_to_telegram(text)\n        sys.exit(0 if ok else 1)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":23,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Send Discord message to Telegram\"\"\"\nimport requests\nimport sys\n\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = \"8674013658:AAEK6ot7k9xxhoBWFXX5MnpWnA6Jru5uE0o\"\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = \"1060942816\"\n\ndef send_to_telegram(text):\n    if text.startswith(\"[TG] \"):\n        return True\n    \n    try:\n        payload = {\n            \"chat_id\": TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID,\n            \"text\": f\"[DC] {text}\"\n        }\n        r = requests.post(\n            f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}/sendMessage\",\n            json=payload,\n            timeout=10\n        )\n        return r.status_code == 200\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return False\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    text = sys.argv[1] if len(sys.argv) > 1 else sys.s