{"type":"message","id":"9ac6e4aa","parentId":"ac2d6a23","timestamp":"2026-05-07T08:38:11.298Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"apt 失败了。让我检查有什么包可用，或者试试其他方法。\n\n也许我应该用 `requests` 库来做 Discord HTTP API 的轮询？Discord 有 `/users/@me/channels/{id}/messages` endpoint，我可以每 2-3 秒 poll 一次。虽然不实时，但对于 bridge 来说够用了，而且不会和任何人冲突。\n\n这比 websocket 简单多了，而且不需要额外依赖。\n\n让我重写 bridge-dc-listener.py 用 HTTP polling Discord DM。\n\nDiscord HTTP API 限制：\n- 每 5 秒最多 5 requests 对于 DM channel\n- 所以每 2 秒 poll 一次是安全的\n\n流程：\n1. 获取 DM channel ID（和之前一样）\n2. 每 2 秒 GET /channels/{id}/messages?limit=5\n3. 跟踪最后处理的消息 ID\n4. 新消息就发到 Telegram\n\n这样完全不需要 websocket！\n\n让我重写脚本。","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.write:43","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/apinan/.openclaw/workspace/bridge-dc-listener.py","content":"#!/usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"\nDiscord -> Telegram auto-relay daemon.\nPolls Discord DM via HTTP API (no WebSocket needed).\nNo extra dependencies beyond requests (usually pre-installed).\n\"\"\"\n\nimport os\nimport sys\nimport json\nimport time\nimport requests\n\nTELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN = \"867401…uE0o\"\nTELEGRAM_CHAT_ID = \"1060942816\"\nTELEGRAM_API = f\"https://api.telegram.org/bot{TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN}\"\n\nDISCORD_TOKEN = os.environ.get(\"DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN\", \"\")\nDISCORD_USER_ID = \"817750913405157406\"\nDISCORD_API = \"https://discord.com/api/v10\"\n\ndef send_to_telegram(text):\n    if text.startswith(\"[TG] \") or text.startswith(\"[DC] \"):\n        return True\n    try:\n        payload = {\"chat_id\": TELEGRAM_CHAT_ID, \"text\": f\"[DC] {text}\"}\n        r = requests.post(f\"{TELEGRAM_API}/sendMessage\", json=payload, timeout=10)\n        if r.status_code == 200:\n            print(f\"[DC->TG] Sent: {text[:50]}\")\n            return True\n        else:\n            print(f\"[DC->TG] Failed: {r.status_code} {r.text}\", file=sys.stderr)\n            return False\n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"[DC->TG] Error: {e}\", file=sys.stderr)\n        return False\n\ndef get_dm_channel():\n    headers = {\n        \"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\",\n        \"Content-Type\": \"application/json\"\n    }\n    r = requests.post(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/users/@me/channels\",\n        headers=headers,\n        json={\"recipient_id\": DISCORD_USER_ID},\n        timeout=10\n    )\n    if r.status_code == 200:\n        cid = r.json().get(\"id\")\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Discord DM channel: {cid}\")\n        return cid\n    else:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Failed to create DM: {r.status_code} {r.text}\")\n        return None\n\ndef poll_discord(channel_id, last_msg_id):\n    headers = {\"Authorization\": f\"Bot {DISCORD_TOKEN}\"}\n    params = {\"limit\": 10}\n    if last_msg_id:\n        params[\"after\"] = last_msg_id\n\n    r = requests.get(\n        f\"{DISCORD_API}/channels/{channel_id}/messages\",\n        headers=headers,\n        params=params,\n        timeout=10\n    )\n    if r.status_code != 200:\n        print(f\"[Bridge] Discord poll error: {r.status_code}\")\n        return last_msg_id, []\n\n    messages = r.json()\n    new_messages = []\n    new_last_id = last_msg_id\n\n    # Discord returns newest first\n    for msg in reversed(messages):\n        mid = msg.get(\"id\")\n        author = msg.get(\"author\", {})\n        text = msg.get(\"content\", \"\")\n\n        # Only from target user, not bot itself, skip empty\n        if str(author.get(\"id\")) == DISCORD_USER_ID and text:\n            if not text.startswith(\"[TG] \"):\n                new_messages.append(text)\n\n        if mid and (not new_last_id or int(mid) > int(new_last_id)):\n            new_last_id = mid\n\n    return new_last_id, new_messages\n\ndef main():\n    if not DISCORD_TOKEN:\n        print(\"[Bridge] ERROR: DISCORD_BOT_TOKEN not set!\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    print(\"[Bridge] Starting Discord -> Telegram relay...\")\n    channel_id = get_dm_channel()\n    if not channel_id:\n        print(\"[Bridge] ERROR: No DM channel. Exiting.\")\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    last_msg_id = None\n    print(\"[Bridge] Polling started (Ctrl+C to stop)\")\n\n    while True:\n        try:\n            last_msg_id, messages = poll_discord(channel_id, last_msg_id)\n            for text in messages:\n                print(f\"[Bridge] DC -> TG: {text[:50]}\")\n                send_to_telegram(text)\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"[Bridge] Error: {e}\")\n\n        time.sleep(2)\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-pay","model":"kimi-k2.6:cloud","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1778143062021,"responseId":"chatcmpl-1778143064674"}}
