{"type":"message","id":"32bf88b7","parentId":"d9d82c3d","timestamp":"2026-05-07T09:23:45.646Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if Discord bots can talk to each other. The user said \"แล้วใน Discord สามารถทำให้บอร์ดคุยกันได้มั้ย\" which translates to \"And in Discord, can you make bots talk to each other?\"\n\nLet me think about this:\n1. Discord bots can technically interact with each other via Discord's API\n2. However, Discord has anti-spam measures that prevent bot-to-bot conversations because it could create infinite loops\n3. If Bot A sends a message, Bot B responds, Bot A responds back, etc. - this creates an infinite loop\n4. Discord actually prevents this by design - bots generally shouldn't respond to other bots\n\nBut what the user might be asking is:\n- Can we have a group chat where multiple bots participate?\n- Can we bridge between multiple Discord bots?\n\nActually, looking at the context, the user is asking about bot-to-bot communication in Discord. The practical answer is:\n1. Yes, technically possible via API\n2. But Discord discourages it to prevent spam/loops\n3. You'd need to implement special logic to prevent infinite loops (e.g., only respond to human messages, ignore bot messages)\n\nSince we're doing a bridge between Telegram and Discord, the user might be asking if we can have the Discord bot relay messages back and forth with other bots.\n\nThe most useful answer would be:\n- Yes, technically possible\n- But need loop prevention\n- Discord bots typically ignore other bots to prevent spam\n- For our bridge, we already prevent loops by skipping bot messages\n\nLet me answer in Thai as per the identity requirements.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"functions.exec:113","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd ~/.openclaw/workspace && python3 tg-to-dc.py \"ได้ครับเจ้านาย แต่ต้องระวัง loop เดี๋ยวผมอธิบาย\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"ollama-p